913,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-20 05:53:21+00:00,22937749,rasbt/mlxtend,5618407,rasbt,,,228560609,302853078,"@vicre

The unittests are run via `nose`. I.e., by navigating into the mlxtend directory and executing `nosetests` (requires the `nose` package).

When I am looking at your log output, there's the line 

    Launching unittests with arguments python -m unittest test_kernel_pca.test_default_components in /home/XXX/git/0ds/mlxtend/mlxtend/feature_extraction/tests

I think that the `unittest` module is generally not compatible with nosetests as they are currently implemented.

I had some plans replacing `nose` by using the `unittest` module some time ago, since it's in the standardlib, which it's generally a nice thing. I use `unittest` in some other projects and don't have any issues with it (just happened that I started this project with using nose); however, I also thought that it might not be worth the effort porting the current tests to `unittest` since `nose` still seems to be quite popular (e.g., scikit-learn among others are using nose).  

That being said, I wouldn't have anything against porting the tests over to unittest, but I thought it might be too time-consuming.",{},,User,False
