1178,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-17 12:18:50+00:00,52478762,etingof/pysnmp,17447359,etingof,,,282640699,352251786,"When SNMP v1 response has `error-status` raised and `error-index` pointing to the problem OID in the *request*, there is no guarantee that the rest of OIDs in response are indeed in good shape. Therefore when you get SNMP v1 response with `error-status` you can't do much but discard everything you got in response. That is the reason why pysnmp sets `endOfMib` sentinel to all the values in the response.

