1917,IssueCommentEvent,2016-12-17 00:51:36+00:00,667289,daler/pybedtools,115406,daler,,,195700011,267730617,"Thanks for reporting. I'm unable to reproduce on Linux and have limited access to a dev OSX machine. I'll try to reproduce on OSX as soon as I get a chance. Are you actually using the command `python setup.py nosetests` indicated at the top of the output? I don't think that's enabled in the setup.py, at least, it won't even run at all for me. Does it work if you just do `nosetests` after installing?

pybedtools is on bioconda if you're just looking to install it (http://bioconda.github.io/).

