3023,IssueCommentEvent,2018-01-10 14:46:02+00:00,1904815,mbi/django-rosetta,363778,jbaldivieso,,,287208446,356623172,"Hi Marco,
I have absolutely no problems with any of your changes; I think this is ready to merge. Thank you for your quick turnaround!

As to the cache invalidation problem: yes, you understand the situation correctly. However, shortening the cache timeout introduces a separate problem. If the catalog-in-cache scenario is used to translate a catalog and then download your work (since it's not being written out to the filesystem), the chances increases significantly of you doing a lot of translating only to have your changes fall out of cache without any indication that that happened.

I'm curious how often this use case is used (if at all?). If it's common enough to warrant more work, it would be nice if there were additional aspects to the interface to serve that use case: indications of when you've diverged from the filesystem, reminders to download an otherwise-unsaved catalog, etc.",{},NONE,User,False
