3055,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-03 21:14:45+00:00,59235,mkleehammer/pyodbc,25211973,v-chojas,,,268423698,341828977,"> Perhaps this is a limitation of  `sp_describe_undeclared_parameters`  when working with temporary tables.

Yes, it appears that the SP does not support temporary tables. Running the call manually after creating the temp table results in an ""invalid object name"" error.

Note that this would succeed if you use an older ODBC driver, like SQL Server (SQLSRV32.DLL), since it does not use that SP to implement SQLDescribeParam --- it uses the deprecated-but-working FMTONLY instead.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
