3060,IssueCommentEvent,2017-02-22 19:22:41+00:00,59235,mkleehammer/pyodbc,1158224,keitherskine,,,209546727,281773426,"""SELECT ... INTO ..."" puts more than just one lock on the database in SQL Server.  Generally, you can't create other objects in the database whilst this kind of statement is running, which might explain the timeout you're getting.  Hence, ""SELECT ... INTO ..."" is something I try to avoid for large amounts of data.  Try running your code above in two steps, as follows:
```sql
-- generate the temporary table (this should be very quick)
SELECT TOP 0 FieldA, FieldB, geometry::UnionAggregate(ShapeBuffer) AS ShapeDissolve
INTO Tmp_Table
FROM (SELECT FieldA, FieldB, Shape.STBuffer(10) AS ShapeBuffer FROM FeatureClass) AS TblA
GROUP BY FieldA, FieldB;

-- populate the temporary table
INSERT INTO Tmp_Table
SELECT FieldA, FieldB, geometry::UnionAggregate(ShapeBuffer) AS ShapeDissolve
FROM (SELECT FieldA, FieldB, Shape.STBuffer(10) AS ShapeBuffer FROM FeatureClass) AS TblA
GROUP BY FieldA, FieldB
```",{},,User,False
