3770,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-28 17:45:47+00:00,13265524,balloob/pychromecast,3463496,wind-rider,,,167967807,235970641,"@balloob I don't understand why you want 1 media controller. The issue is that some chromecast apps do not talk the protocol of the ""Default media receiver app"".

So for play/pause in ds audio I need pychromecast to send different messages than to the default app.

Besides it needs an authentication in the ""connected""

Also the ""status update messages"" are different from the MediaStatus messages (although there is some overlap)

I would say that controllers should preferably have a common interface (all controllers should have a play method, a pause method, etc) with feature detection which features are supported

The appropriate controller for the current app could then be loaded in a property of the pychromecast client.

HomeAssistant should then be able to call play or pause without knowing what the implementation is. Simply using the default media controller for all apps does not work...",{},,User,False
