4126,IssueCommentEvent,2016-10-08 08:12:51+00:00,6054289,niklasf/python-chess,402777,niklasf,,,181800265,252410907,"Hi. To clarify: Reverse order is not nescessarily faster, but it makes information from later positions available in the hashtable. You can iterate in reverse order this way:

```
node = node.end()
while node:
    print(node.move)
    node = node.parent
```

One potential pitfall: `info_handler.info` will get updated with information from the latest search and your above snippet will always reference that latest info. Be sure to make actual copies (e.g. `import copy; temp_score = copy.copy(info_handler.info)`).",{},,User,False
