4305,IssueCommentEvent,2018-01-12 00:56:13+00:00,21476229,deanmalmgren/textract,5474426,MalikRumi,,,80844213,357111008,"Ok, I am going to ask a naive question here, and I hope you don't mind enlightening me. I tried your script in a python for loop, and was surprised to find I couldn't make it work. That is what led me here. It is one thing to say some sort of internal for loop is 'extra', I get that, but why doesn't it work in a regular Python for loop? That I **don't** get. Of course, it is entirely possible I just did it wrong. Nah, that can't be it. But your bash loop **does** work. Same for all the output going to a single file, instead of one output file for each input file, but that part I was able to figure out. Thanks for sharing your insight, wisdom and experience with me!",{},NONE,User,False
