4315,IssueCommentEvent,2015-03-04 23:12:20+00:00,3343080,erikrose/parsimonious,295816,erikrose,,,59605214,77271405,"```
reserved_keyword = ""def"" / ""class""
identifier = !reserved_keyword ""name""
```

`name` is a ""name""-type token. It would have been tokenized by whatever pre-processing phase we're talking about, prior to calling Parsimonious. It would probably have a `text` attr or something containing its actual char string.

In other words, I'm proposing an entirely tokenized input sequence, not some hybrid of tokens and string chunks.",{},,User,False
