4355,IssueCommentEvent,2018-01-03 12:32:08+00:00,24561828,gunthercox/ChatterBot,13664257,vkosuri,,,285669092,355001299,"Try to change statement comparison methods to get better results http://chatterbot.readthedocs.io/en/stable/comparisons.html#statement-comparison

``` Python
# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
from chatterbot import ChatBot

# Create a new chat bot named Charlie
chatbot = ChatBot(
    'Charlie',
    trainer='chatterbot.trainers.ListTrainer',
    logic_adapters=[
        {
            ""import_path"": ""chatterbot.logic.BestMatch"",
            ""statement_comparison_function"": ""chatterbot.comparisons.jaccard_similarity"",
            ""response_selection_method"": ""chatterbot.response_selection.get_first_response""
        },
        {
            'import_path': 'chatterbot.logic.LowConfidenceAdapter',
            'threshold': 0.65,
            'default_response': ""I didn't understand that question; do you need help with Math, Excel, Music or Graphic?""
        }
    ]
)

chatbot.train([
    ""I need help with Photoshop"",
    ""Here is the link to Photoshop 123"",
    ""Excel"",
    ""Hey I see you need help with Microsoft Excel please click on the following link Etc"",
    ""Math"",
    ""Hey I see you need help with Math please click on the following link Etc"",
    ""Graphic"",
    ""Hey I see you need help with Graphic please click on the following link Etc"",
    ""Music"",
    ""Hey I see you need help with Music please click on the following link Etc""
])

# Get a response to the input text 'How are you?'
response = chatbot.get_response('I need help with Math')
print(response)
response = chatbot.get_response('Excel')
print(response)
```",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
