4737,IssueCommentEvent,2015-12-11 19:23:02+00:00,28835957,geowurster/NewlineJSON,2676083,geowurster,,,121771672,164025510,"@arowla `NewlineJSON` is primarily an I/O library so the CLI is a bonus tool for simple, common format translations, which is why it is only accessed through `python -m` instead of via a standalone utility.  Since the CLI isn't designed to be a core feature, the `click` dependency is optional - installing with `pip install newlinejson[cli]` will bring in the additional dependency.  Depending on your shell, you may have to escape the square brackets.

`pip` isn't very good about advertising this feature, so I'll add a note to the readme.",{},,User,False
