5511,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-05 11:48:47+00:00,83844720,ageitgey/face_recognition,26684313,sluongng,,,233527509,306169216,"it seems like the problem is with `scipy.misc.imread`

Quick google search give you this https://docs.scipy.org/doc/scipy-0.18.1/reference/generated/scipy.misc.imread.html where it stated that there is no such `mode` with value `mode`.

```
mode can be one of the following strings:

- ‘L’ (8-bit pixels, black and white)
- ‘P’ (8-bit pixels, mapped to any other mode using a color palette)
- ‘RGB’ (3x8-bit pixels, true color)
- ‘RGBA’ (4x8-bit pixels, true color with transparency mask)
- ‘CMYK’ (4x8-bit pixels, color separation)
- ‘YCbCr’ (3x8-bit pixels, color video format)
- ‘I’ (32-bit signed integer pixels)
