5721,IssueCommentEvent,2017-08-17 01:02:24+00:00,100263581,sammchardy/python-binance,6649065,sammchardy,,,250797258,322940131,"Hey @dmacmillan,

Essentially this is a CORS error and means that the Binance API isn't returning and 'Access-Control-Allow-Origin' header, or with a value that includes your server.
I assume you're using Chrome which is restricting these type of requests be default. You will probably find that Firefox will work.

For now you can add a Chrome plugin which disables this check
something like [this plugin](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/allow-control-allow-origi/nlfbmbojpeacfghkpbjhddihlkkiljbi?hl=en) or [this one](), or search CORS on the [Chrome Webstore](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/).

A more general solution would be to submit a request to Binance to update their API response headers to include an 'Access-Control-Allow-Origin' header ideally with value '*' allowing all hosts.

If you send the requests server side you won't have any issues, it's only from the browser.

Hope that helps.",{},,User,False
