5763,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-20 00:38:11+00:00,12420595,CamDavidsonPilon/lifelines,884032,CamDavidsonPilon,,,275136063,345564357,"The introduction of this comes at a cost which I believe out ways the benefit. `KaplanMeierFitter.fit` is one of the most commonly used functions, and to add another parameter, even a keyword parameter, should be treated as having a high user cost. Too many parameters and users get confused and make the wrong choice. In this case, the same functionality can be achieved _outside_ the function too:

```python
kmf = KaplanMeierFitter()
E_not = ~E
kmf.fit(T, E_not)
kmf.plot()
...
```

So I would prefer users to do that behaviour, rather than lifelines takes are of it. ",{},OWNER,User,False
