6104,IssueCommentEvent,2015-04-24 02:00:05+00:00,32092611,ionelmc/python-appengine-sdk,67686,gmunkhbaatarmn,,,70209026,95773525,"After run:
`coverage run dev_appserver.py project_root`
Can't collect coverage datas. 

> This doesn't work on current versions of GAE. They do some sandboxing within the code run for GAE (eg disable loading of binary modules, remove modules and methods not supported on the servers). coverage now produces data for everything except the actual application code!
> Source: http://stackoverflow.com/q/5800674/287255

But by using `old_dev_appserver.py` [can collect](http://stackoverflow.com/a/18691320/287255) coverage datas.
So reason of using 1.9.15 is, after v1.9.15 (from v1.9.16) `old_dev_appserver.py` not included in App Engine SDK.

Here is my currently using coverage running script:
```
coverage run -p --source=./ old_dev_appserver . --skip_sdk_update_check --clear_datastore --use_sqlite --port=8081 &> dev_appserver.log &
coverage run -p tests.py --source=./
coverage combine
coverage report ./*.py ./modules/*.py
```",{},,User,False
