6355,IssueCommentEvent,2018-02-08 17:59:00+00:00,26947860,facelessuser/pymdown-extensions,1055125,facelessuser,,,211150081,364195835,"These aren't used anymore:

```
        'uml_flow': [True, ""Enable flowcharts - Default: True""],
        'uml_sequence': [True, ""Enable sequence diagrams - Default: True""],
```

See documentation: https://facelessuser.github.io/pymdown-extensions/extensions/superfences/#options.  So adding a mermaid specific option here does nothing.  Scan the code, we don't actually use `uml_flow` or `uml_sequence` to do anything, so adding `mermaid` will also do nothing.  Those logic behind those options were deprecated and removed.  I should go ahead remove the actual parameters as well.

So `custom_fences` is the only way to affect the extension in this way, and there should be no need to hard code a mermaid option in the library, you should be able to specify it in your mkdocs.yml file.  When I have time I can verify that with your other settings, but there is no need for a hard coded mermaid option.",{},OWNER,User,False
