6794,IssueCommentEvent,2018-01-24 18:35:44+00:00,81221757,ethereum/eth-utils,205327,carver,6250754,ethereum,291054734,360230726,"> AttributeDict to it's own package if we have a secondary use case for it.
HexBytes to it's own package if we have a secondary use case for it.

Since `eth-account` will be a proper end-user package (you could theoretically use it without web3), I'd like to keep returning values in friendly ways. That means joint key and attribute access (`AttributeDict`), and pretty display of `bytes` at the console (`HexBytes`).

I don't know if I will have the time to make separate packages for each of those, so maybe I'll just copy the data structures into eth-account for now if you are hesitant to add them to eth-utils.

---

Another one came up: the formatting appliers, like `apply_formatters_to_dict`.

That's used for converting values in a user-supplied transaction dict to a consistent type.",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
