6819,IssueCommentEvent,2015-05-14 20:59:07+00:00,318058,twisted/txmongo,909638,IlyaSkriblovsky,716546,twisted,76483340,102167723,"Cool!

I've looked into sporadically failed tests and found that this happens for tests that create `MongoConnection` and immediately call its `disconnect()` without issuing any queries. `MongoConnection()` constructor starts connecting in background. Connection process in turn starts name resolution of ""localhost"" into ip-address. If name resolution doesn't finish until `disconnect()` returns (it takes exactly 1 main loop round-trip), trial fails with ""reactor unclean"". (Name resolution is deferred to separate thread, so there is race condition which fails more often on slow machines).

Unfortunately, I didn't found any good way to wait until name resolution is done :(

The simpliest way to solve this is to change ""localhost"" to ""127.0.0.1"" in `test_queries.py` and `test_aggregate.py`. Or to issue any command on `MongoConnection` in corresponding test methods.",{},,User,False
6820,IssueCommentEvent,2016-04-15 02:22:59+00:00,318058,twisted/txmongo,5890272,linearb,716546,twisted,148470691,210255951,"Ok - thanks. It'd be good to get support for read preference in sometime.

I guess there is a bit so far: in connection.py when read preference in
the options is primary or primary preferred it immediately configures and gets all the 
members of the replset--- so it fails over when the primary changes or fails. 

Surprisingly, I noticed that when read preference is secondary it doesn't configure and 
get all the members of the replset. Is that behavior expected? I would have thought that 
the task looping call would have run.


",{},,User,False
