6953,IssueCommentEvent,2016-03-07 09:48:11+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,61316,milliams,13271048,ganga-devs,138522205,193183473,"As @drmarkwslater said, my plan for the next release (6.1.18 or after) is to add a `flush_soon` queue to the registry flusher which will schedule a flush of that object to happen in the next second or so. This allows us to centralise the calls to `_flush` in one place (Registry.py) and also desynchronises the call so that it doesn't slow down submission. Whether we would then want a ""really flush right now and I will wait until it's finished"" call during `Job.submit` is up for discussion.",{},,User,False
