7072,IssueCommentEvent,2016-01-11 13:40:14+00:00,27823188,aldryn/aldryn-newsblog,994951,czpython,4201738,aldryn,116844419,170551622,"@trawick Django migrations are extremely sensitive.

Example:

```python
field = models.CharField(choices=settings.LANGUAGES)
```

If I create a migration for the field above and then add or remove a language from
``settings.LANGUAGES``, Django will report that there's a migration missing, this is because the ``settings.LANGUAGES``  has changed.

So for these third party addons its tricky because they're run under different projects with different settings.

If possible, please generate the migrations and compare them to the previous ones, it's the only way to know if a substantial change has happened.",{},,User,False
