7496,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-07 20:35:17+00:00,120541397,openai/retro,4770482,praveen-palanisamy,14957082,openai,312203892,379497390,"Seems like the [retro/retro/scripts/playback_movie.py](https://github.com/openai/retro/blob/1363ed6825ac836d3a7e57919ef0984a9ccc0ff6/retro/scripts/playback_movie.py) script is broken.

The `AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'terminate'` is coming from [this line](https://github.com/openai/retro/blob/1363ed6825ac836d3a7e57919ef0984a9ccc0ff6/retro/scripts/playback_movie.py#L40):
`viewer_proc.terminate()`

The `viewer_proc` does not exist because the `viewer` object is `None` and that is because the `--viewer` argument is not set when the `playback_movie.py`'s `main()` is called.

### Fix 1: I modified the `killprocs(...)` method like below:

```
def killprocs(*args, **kwargs):
    ffmpeg_proc.terminate()
    if viewer:
        viewer_proc.terminate()
    viewer_proc.wait()
    raise BrokenPipeError
```
There is also this error/warning: 
` [aac @ 0x215c2a0] The encoder 'aac' is experimental but experimental codecs are not enabled, add '-strict -2' if you want to use it.`

### Fix2: So I changed [line 27](https://github.com/openai/retro/blob/1363ed6825ac836d3a7e57919ef0984a9ccc0ff6/retro/scripts/playback_movie.py#L27) to this:
` ffmpeg_proc = subprocess.Popen(['ffmpeg', '-y', 'strict', '-2',`

The `playback_movie.py` script now runs fine but it does not seem to generate a valid `*.mp4` file. I haven't looked any deeper that that.

",{},NONE,User,False
