7509,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-31 09:42:36+00:00,92238803,openai/baselines,9654655,albarji,14957082,openai,333064550,409161084,"Oh, you are right! I thought this clipping always made the difference (vpred - R) smaller, but looking again at the code it seems R = advantage + OLDPRED. In the clipped loss you are using a clipped vpred that cannot deviate much from OLDPRED, but you still have the influence of the advantage in R.

So, I guess even if the network is updated so that the value prediction is perfect (vpred == OLDPRED + advantage) you will still suffer some loss if the change in predicted value is large. I imagine this has a similar effect as the one clipping presented in the PPO paper for the PG loss.",{},NONE,User,False
