7643,IssueCommentEvent,2015-08-31 15:33:59+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,73019,mboersma,6117407,deis,101281474,136407665,"> We should investigate `iptables: No chain/target/match by that name.`

This happens when running the rules for the first time; since they are meant to be idempotent, the script tries to flush custom rules that don't yet exist:
```sh
# Flush custom rules before the restore (so this script is idempotent)
sudo /usr/sbin/iptables -F Firewall-INPUT
```
So it's not an error and can be ignored. @aledbf may work on a PR to silence the error message in this case.",{},,User,False
