8229,IssueCommentEvent,2017-02-27 13:11:04+00:00,33952074,pytest-dev/pytest-html,122800,davehunt,8897583,pytest-dev,210452824,282715865,"@sylvinus let me know if the new commits to #104 work for you. If so, I'll hopefully be doing a release later today.",{},,User,False
8232,IssueCommentEvent,2017-07-28 19:44:47+00:00,41756998,pytest-dev/pytest-xdist,1628587,carlos-jenkins,8897583,pytest-dev,244524346,318745295,"> I hope I'm not coming across as trying to shoot down your efforts, I'm just trying to brainstorm with everyone involved here to see if perhaps we can get to a better/more general implementation.

Not at all. I appreciate the time you took to explain more use cases, I was unaware of them, and indeed I agree with you, implementation of grouping based on markers seems the correct approach. 

The deal breaker for me was that the markers had to be put manually, but as you explained if the possibility of marking could be done programmatically, in a transparent way to the user, using ``pytest_collect_modifyitems`` even with a default behavior defined by the argument ``group-by``, then it provides a even more flexible framework for distributing tests.

Sadly, I'm unable to help you implementing grouping in this way, I still think this will imply larger changes to the way xdist works, larger changes in the current schedulers, workflow and testing than I'm able to help realize.

I'm closing this PR and will be maintaining the fork if anyone needs this functionality in the immediate term, hopefully grouping gets into the core someday and we will be able to drop the fork.

Thanks.",{},,User,False
