8336,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-27 14:09:06+00:00,24993138,google/brotli,2976776,torappinfo,1342004,google,327690518,408429838,"I'v compressed every 64k block of a large file with brotli and then concatenate them together. The compressed file has a header to provide offsets for each blocks. 
The header format is as follows:
```
struct CONTENT_LOC {
  ub1 offset[5];
};

struct HEADER {
  byte flags;
  CONTENT_LOC len_decompressed; //length of original uncompressed file
  CONTENT_LOC blocks[]; //offsets for each blocks, CONTENT_LOC[nBlocks+1] 
};

```
Here nBlocks=(len_decompressed-1)/64k + 1. 

In this format, BrotliDecoderDecompress() crashed for the very first block for my testing data.

