8338,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-23 17:03:06+00:00,24993138,google/brotli,1151,nemequ,1342004,google,160303707,234728813,"Virtually everything should be working now (see https://travis-ci.org/nemequ/brotli/builds/146808543).  The only real hole is TSan, which I don't think is going to happen on 12.04… between an ancient version of CMake and updated compilers which expect newer binutils, there are just too many problems :(.  I'm sure I could get it working on 14.04, but if you want to use Travis' container infrastructure 12.04 is required, and given the number of different builds I think the container infrastructure is definitely a good idea.

