8616,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-19 16:32:55+00:00,71996613,blue-yonder/tsfresh,6900225,kr1stjans,6234170,blue-yonder,226863124,302750790,"I disagree that target vector should only contain two values for two samples.

Target vector is independent of the number of samples. Target vector in the documentation is 0 and 1 only because there are two states (robot reports a failure or not). If we have one, two or n robots, the target vector would still have only two values.

In the different scenario, the target vector could be robot's electricity consumption. Target vector values would therefore be any real number or integer number (electricity consumption can be 1 Wh, 2Wh, 100Wh, 1000Wh, independently of the number of robots). One, two or n robots could have all those values.

I just recently discovered tsfresh, so correct me if I'm wrong, but this is how I understand it.",{},,User,False
