8715,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-26 13:51:40+00:00,63484632,facebookresearch/fastText,1772912,ericxsun,16943930,facebookresearch,293514828,376173007,"@matanster incremental training actually means, having finished training model with data we got before, and retrain the model with newer data we get, **not from scratch**. 

When training word embedding, you could do it from scratch with all data at each time, or just on the new data. For classification, you could train it from scratch with pre-trained word embedding with all data, or only the new one, with no changing of the word embedding. It's all Okay.",{},NONE,User,False
8739,IssueCommentEvent,2016-10-19 15:19:55+00:00,63484632,facebookresearch/fastText,10580847,spate141,16943930,facebookresearch,183737609,254845625,"fastText recognize labels with that `__label__` tag, (or you can define your own, as describe on readme file)

