9448,IssueCommentEvent,2015-08-03 18:59:48+00:00,33653601,jupyter/notebook,327925,takluyver,7388996,jupyter,98671332,127370628,"There are a couple of ways you could do something like this:

- Configure a post-save hook that runs git commit every time a notebook is saved. I don't think that sees a distinction between a user-initiated save and an autosave, though.
- Write a [contents manager](http://jupyter-notebook.readthedocs.org/en/latest/extending/contents.html) (@ssanderson: thanks for those docs) to store notebooks in Git.

I don't think we have any plans to do this ourselves.",{},,User,False
