9698,IssueCommentEvent,2015-10-30 21:13:24+00:00,24774658,boto/boto3,368057,jamesls,327752,boto,114137508,152652826,"@kengruven We need to update our docs.  We recently added support for this, so make sure you're using the latest botocore version.  You can set these in your `~/.aws/config` file to get equivalent behavior for `OrdinaryCallingFormat`:

```
[default]
s3=
    addressing_style = path
```

The indentation in front of `addressing_style` is relevant.  For reference, subdomain would be:

```
[default]
s3=
    addressing_style = virtual
```

Until we get the docs updated, here's the relevant docstring from botocore: https://github.com/boto/botocore/blob/develop/botocore/client.py#L627

Let us know if `addressing_style=path` doesn't work with the fakes3.",{},,User,False
