9719,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-03 20:02:08+00:00,24774658,boto/boto3,4605355,kyleknap,327752,boto,224186459,299019177,"Thanks for the detailed summary! It's very helpful. It does not look like an issue with boto3. The string that it signs are correct with respect to ensuring it signs the ACL value in presigned url correctly. The discrepancies you are noticing appear to be S3's behavior with respect to the policy you are using and when differing parameters in the querystring and headers are provided.

I would recommend opening a thread on this in the [AWS Developer Forums](https://forums.aws.amazon.com/forum.jspa?forumID=24) as well, but if I were to guess for each scenario:

1) **Presigned PUT URL with header gets created public read:** It passes your  bucket policy because the header had the bucket-owner-full-control. However when S3 processes it, it notices both acl's and sets the two because they are valid to coexist. I am confused though why it sets the bucket ownership to that of Account A. It seems that it should be for Account B.
2) **Presigned PUT URL - without header but with ACL gets denied:** This fails your bucket policy because the request did not have the x-amz-acl header. Having it in the query string is not enough to pass the bucket policy.
3) **Presigned PUT URL with header and without ACL Specified gets denied:** This is actually a signature mismatch 403. You are providing the x-amz-acl header in the request but not having it signed in the query string and since it is required for all x-amz headers to be signed, S3 will calculate a signature mismatch.
4) **Presigned PUT URL with header and with ACL:** Yep that should work.
5) **Presigned PUT URL with header doesn't grant Bucket Owner Permissions:** It passes your bucket policy because the header is present, but the private value clobbers/takes precedence over the bucket-owner-full-control.

I have a feeling all of this behavior has to do with the fact you are using sigv2. I would recommend upgrading your policy to only allow sigv4. Testing the scenarios you listed with sigv4. I got 403's for all of the scenarios you listed but number 4, which should be correct. Would that be possible?

",{},,User,False
