9728,IssueCommentEvent,2017-04-20 06:41:42+00:00,6670942,boto/botocore,16921683,brianfaull,327752,boto,179833070,295599234,"There are a couple additional ""gotchas"" that I ran into (unless I'm missing something else).

* When using `LastEvaluatedKey`, **you must ensure that `PaginationConfig['MaxItems']` is evenly divisible by `PaginationConfig['PageSize']`**. If it is not, in the last retrieved page the `Count`/`ScannedCount` will not be equal to `len(page['Items'])`, and `page['LastEvaluatedKey']` will not be consistent with the final item in the Items list. It's not clear to me why (in the absence of `ScanFilter`) that those would not be equal, but that is the case for the last page when MaxItems mod PageSize != 0. I ran into this because I was using a heuristic to figure out ""about how many items I could process in time_interval"", and I was missing data on the boundaries. It's not clear if this is intentional or not, and it's not clear if `restore_token` would have the same behavior or not.
* **Using `page['LastEvaluatedKey']` forces you to use the `Client.scan()` interface (as `ExclusiveStartKey={'field': {'S': 'value'}}`** (i.e., you can't use the `Paginator.Scan.paginate()` interface, because there's nowhere to bootstrap a `paginate()` with something like `LastEvaluatedKey`).  That is, `paginate()` expects the `paginator.restore_token`, a string token rather than a DDB attribute-value dict as returned by `LastEvaluatedKey`. As an aside, the docs don't even say that `paginate()`'s response includes `LastEvaluatedKey` and as far as I can tell it is not useful. An example is here: https://github.com/boto/boto3/issues/954",{},,User,False
9730,IssueCommentEvent,2017-02-07 22:55:56+00:00,6670942,boto/botocore,2643092,JordonPhillips,327752,boto,203572733,278171485,"""execute-api"" isn't an AWS service - it's an implementation detail related to API Gateway's functionality. The api's you would use that for are not AWS services.

To answer your question, `get_available_services` is intended to list supported services for the version of boto3 / botocore you have installed. For a more complete list of supported services, see [this page](https://aws.amazon.com/products/). Since you're interested in signing, you might also be interested in the list of regions and endpoints for each service [here](http://docs.aws.amazon.com/general/latest/gr/rande.html).",{},,User,False
