10309,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-08 17:17:52+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,22928517,aanandr,6844498,Azure,226727966,299930805,"I don’t know why this happens. How do we debug this further? Also, I didn’t follow what you meant about the order in which the command is executed with IDs and names.

From: Travis Prescott [mailto:notifications@github.com]
Sent: Monday, May 8, 2017 10:08 AM
To: Azure/azure-cli <azure-cli@noreply.github.com>
Cc: Aanand Ramachandran <aanandr@microsoft.com>; Author <author@noreply.github.com>
Subject: Re: [Azure/azure-cli] az network vpn-connection delete doesnt seem to be working when the conn name and RG are specified but works when resource ID of the connection is specified (#3228)


The following command outputs clearly points out that delete is not working

DELETING THE CONNECTIONS
az network vpn-connection delete -n VNet1VNet4 -g TestRG1 --verbose --debug
Starting long running operation 'Starting network vpn-connection delete'
https://management.azure.com:443<https://na01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmanagement.azure.com%3A443&data=02%7C01%7Caanandr%40microsoft.com%7C6cb5b136dd2849e60a8608d49634c33d%7C72f988bf86f141af91ab2d7cd011db47%7C1%7C0%7C636298600742403144&sdata=byZB86yk1CmWTzdarISALO0uDjXbqsQmkvBnkxXEuVM%3D&reserved=0> ""DELETE /subscriptions/d6ff83d6-713d-41f6-a025-5eb76334fda9/resourceGroups/TestRG1/providers/Microsoft.Network/connections/VNet1VNet4?api-version=2016-09-01 HTTP/1.1"" 204 0
msrest.http_logger : Response status: 204
Long running operation 'Starting network vpn-connection delete' completed with result None

CONNECTIONS STILL THERE
az network vpn-connection list -g TestRG1

SPECIFYING THE ENTIRE RESOURCE ID HELPS AND THE CONNECTIONS GET DELETED
az network vpn-connection delete --ids /subscriptions/d6ff83d6-713d-41f6-a025-5eb76334fda9/resourceGroups/TestRG1/providers/Microsoft.Network/connections/VNet1ToVNet4 --debug --verbose
Starting long running operation 'Starting network vpn-connection delete'
https://management.azure.com:443<https://na01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmanagement.azure.com%3A443&data=02%7C01%7Caanandr%40microsoft.com%7C6cb5b136dd2849e60a8608d49634c33d%7C72f988bf86f141af91ab2d7cd011db47%7C1%7C0%7C636298600742403144&sdata=byZB86yk1CmWTzdarISALO0uDjXbqsQmkvBnkxXEuVM%3D&reserved=0> ""DELETE /subscriptions/d6ff83d6-713d-41f6-a025-5eb76334fda9/resourceGroups/TestRG1/providers/Microsoft.Network/connections/VNet1ToVNet4?api-version=2016-09-01 HTTP/1.1"" 202 0
msrest.http_logger : Response status: 202

So if you compare the URLs in both cases (names or IDs), the DELETE URLs are the same. This means there is no bug in the CLI as far as handling names or IDs works. If you had tried IDs first and then names, or names twice you would likely have gotten the same results.

Both calls return success from the service. The difference is only the code (204--completed with no content, vs 202--accepted).

