10559,IssueCommentEvent,2015-10-05 21:31:08+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,157586,jsirois,3065172,pantsbuild,108928495,145674380,"It looks like the layers are about right and I can do 2 things to allow experimentation with both inlining and dynamic traversal:
1. Switch from annotating values with Addressed to annotating a class with addressable properties - this removes memory bloat byt lifting the schema for addressable links to the class definition itself - ie in the current world - just 2 types, Configuration and Target, consisting of 2 (extends, merges) and 2 (configurations, dependencies) fields respectively in the schemas - stored in the types themselves once.
2. Add a Resolvable value type that has a single resolve method.  The inline case call resolve, the traversing case does not and instead re-populates the addressable field with one or more Resolvable instances that plumb back through the Graph or its AddressMapper such that property access of these values causes dynamic resolves.

Should have a clean RB by tonight - I have all the pieces working locally.",{},,User,False
