10879,IssueCommentEvent,2018-02-03 01:00:57+00:00,43023379,hackingmaterials/atomate,986759,computron,14116185,hackingmaterials,265357599,362756334,"@bocklund I wanted to follow up on this issue

I can see why defusing the children when the parent calculation has a problem is a bit confusing. I pushed a commit (ba8bdb21f8c221c663bded46710a73ccc71c7f84) that adds an option in the ``config.py`` that lets you control the default behavior of this setting. Furthermore, the default is changed so that the parent job (the one with the problem) is marked as FIZZLED rather than defusing the children.

see config.py:

```
DEFUSE_UNSUCCESSFUL = ""fizzle""  # this is a three-way toggle on what to do if your job looks OK, but is actually unconverged (either electronic or ionic). True -> mark job as COMPLETED, but defuse children. False --> do nothing, continue with workflow as normal. ""fizzle"" --> throw an error (mark this job as FIZZLED)
```

The error that's thrown by default should explain what failed.

I am going to close this for now, but let me know if you want to reopen (or submit another issue).",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
