11131,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-29 15:37:04+00:00,121640861,jupyterhub/chartpress,3837114,consideRatio,17927519,jupyterhub,355201806,416998858,"# Concreter usage example

## Old script
This old script could do an upgrade using a z2jh cloned repo with changes as chart.

```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -eu # exit on error or unset variable
source environment.env

LOCAL_CHART_PATH=""../../z2jh-extended/z2jh""
LOCAL_DIR=""$(pwd)""
# The amount of commits look back on for changes affecting build of images
COMMIT_DEPTH=3

cd $LOCAL_CHART_PATH
chartpress --image-prefix ""consideratio/k8s-"" --push --commit-range HEAD~$COMMIT_DEPTH..HEAD
cd ""$LOCAL_DIR""
helm upgrade $RELEASE --install $LOCAL_CHART_PATH/jupyterhub \
  --namespace $NAMESPACE \
  --values secret-config.yaml \
  --values config.yaml
```

## New script
This script could do the same, but using a local `chartpress-overrides.yaml` and passing an option, the z2jh clone could remain unaffected.

```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -eu # exit on error or unset variable
source environment.env

LOCAL_CHART_PATH=""../../z2jh-extended/z2jh""
# The amount of commits look back on for changes affecting build of images
COMMIT_DEPTH=3

chartpress \
  --values ""chartpress-overrides.yaml"" \
  --image-config image-config.yaml \
  --push \
  --commit-range HEAD~$COMMIT_DEPTH..HEAD

helm upgrade $RELEASE --install $LOCAL_CHART_PATH/jupyterhub \
  --namespace $NAMESPACE \
  --values image
  --values secret-config.yaml \
  --values config.yaml
```",{},MEMBER,User,False
