11535,IssueCommentEvent,2018-02-07 01:01:05+00:00,9801644,elastic/elasticsearch-py,32132,HonzaKral,6764390,elastic,294967068,363619579,"You can rewrite your function to generate (using a `yield` statement) the events and then feed that generator to one of the bulk helpers (0) which will automatically batch it and send it to elasticsearch. I would also suggest having a look at scripted updates in elasticsearch, especially in combination with `upsert` operations that could greatly simplify and speed up your dataflow (1, 2).

You might also want to leave the index creation to elasticsearch using the auto-create functionality along with index templates to control the index settings, that will eliminate another round trip (3)

Hope this helps!

0 - http://elasticsearch-py.readthedocs.io/en/master/helpers.html#elasticsearch.helpers.streaming_bulk
1 - https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/docs-update.html#_scripted_updates
2 - https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/docs-update.html#upserts
3 - https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/indices-templates.html",{},MEMBER,User,False
