11633,IssueCommentEvent,2018-01-23 03:46:27+00:00,40328394,angr/angr,2498805,rhelmot,12520807,angr,290699197,359667591,"Veritesting definitely doesn't just solve all the problems. For an obvious example, look at the grub bug example in angr-doc/examples. If you try to run that without the ""intelligent"" part and with veritesting instead, it'll slow to a crawl and not find anything. The much better solution is, like in the grub example, the application of human intelligence codified into simple rules that match the territory of the problem you're trying to solve.",{},OWNER,User,False
11637,IssueCommentEvent,2016-02-21 06:27:18+00:00,13027352,angr/pyvex,3453847,zardus,12520807,angr,128427160,186758256,"Ah, awesome! Sorry we didn't get to it; we've been pushing super hard toward a conference deadline.

It's interesting that vex doesn't except out when it's not given a jump delay slot, but I guess they never considered a situation where that would be the case. It'll be interesting if it's possible to craft a basic block that is just at the edge of Valgrind's block size limit so that the branch delay slot isn't included, trigger this bug, and detect Valgrind. There are plenty of other ways to do that, of course, but it'd be cool.",{},,User,False
