12060,IssueCommentEvent,2018-06-28 12:20:10+00:00,65684521,astropy/astropy-healpix,2789820,mhvk,847984,astropy,317056313,401015509,"@cdeil - feel free to ping when you really start implementing the ufuncs. Being not much of a C programmer myself, the main thing that tripped me up was that one has to ensure that items passed in to `PyUFunc_FromFuncAndDataAndSignature` are kept in memory, i.e., are static variables (or use memory explicitly allocated). Obviously, the examples do this right, but without comment. 

