12224,IssueCommentEvent,2017-09-21 14:22:29+00:00,1446474,pypa/virtualenv,1110419,pfmoore,647025,pypa,259325733,331171961,"I suspect the issue may be that pyqt5 has started linking to `python3.dll` rather than `python36.dll`. I'm not sure why they chose to do that, but it may be that's what's made this issue start to come up more often. I'm not saying it's a bad thing that they do that, but historically the stable ABI hasn't been used much, which is likely why tools are having to catch up (I suspect pyqt5 have had to customise their build process to do this, AFAIK setuptools doesn't support using the stable ABI out of the box yet).

See https://github.com/pypa/pip/issues/4445 for another aspect of this issue, which I found via a Google search (and explains why the fact that it's pyqt5 seemed familiar to me :smile:)",{},OWNER,User,False
12225,IssueCommentEvent,2015-01-12 07:28:02+00:00,1446474,pypa/virtualenv,159967,mgedmin,647025,pypa,53358848,69536293,"> This breaks tox --recreate.

Actually, `tox -e py33` doesn't work at all, even without --recreate: tox creates a `.tox/py33/log/py33-0.log` *before* it tries to create a virtualenv in `.tox/py33` and this is enough to trigger a *ValueError:  Directory exists* in Python 3.3's venv.",{},,User,False
12228,IssueCommentEvent,2015-02-23 10:39:42+00:00,1446474,pypa/virtualenv,4742081,wm75,647025,pypa,58565462,75520602,"concerning 1: that would be ok
concerning 2: the consequences of an existing pyvenf.cfg file are described as part of [PEP405](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0405/#id19). Before Python3.3 that file is not looked for, with 3.3+ the current rewrite branch (generating the file) proves that it is not causing any harm.

I leave point 3 up for discussion here.",{},,User,False
