12457,IssueCommentEvent,2016-01-21 14:51:36+00:00,4978045,Parsely/pykafka,1626054,ottomata,779641,Parsely,123712410,173594084,"+1 about not padding messages.  It also gives me bad feelings. :)



On Wed, Jan 20, 2016 at 7:06 PM, John Dennison <notifications@github.com>
wrote:

> The idea of padding a message payload gives me bad feelings. It reduces
> interoperability between different consumers in kafka cluster and strikes
> me as magical. Another approach is to give hooks for users to register
> SerDe's. This is the approach samza takes and it gives maximum flexibility
> without touching the bytes in kafka.
>
> Basically you could register a de/serializer for you producer/consumer.
>
> def my_custom_serializer(msg):
>     """"""""Transforms all msg fields into raw bytes""""""
>     msg.value = json.dumps(msg.value).encode()
>
> def my_custom_deserializer(msg):
>     """"""""Transforms msg fields into python objects""""""
>     msg.value = json.loads(msg.value.decode())
>
>
> topic.get_producer(deserializer=my_custom_serializer)
