12793,IssueCommentEvent,2017-09-07 22:38:05+00:00,12898486,juju/charm-tools,529748,codersquid,4604548,juju,224728580,327945688,This is affecting me too.,{},NONE,User,False
12794,IssueCommentEvent,2015-12-02 15:54:49+00:00,12898486,juju/charm-tools,406082,johnsca,4604548,juju,119969693,161342525,"Some overlap with #56.

I'm actually not sure that we should be delving in and inspecting the `interface.yaml`, because then we open ourselves up to an issue similar to the one I have from time to time with `juju deploy` from a local repo, where if you have two charm directories with the same charm name in the `metadata.yaml` (e.g., if I renamed one to ""$charm.old"" for testing purposes), it will pick one at random and is neither consistent nor obvious.  In that case, I end up with what looks like a successful deploy, but it's using the wrong charm code (or would use the wrong interface code, in this case), which is hard to spot and can cause subtle bugs.

We could sort of work around this by sorting the directory names when performing the search so that it's at least consistent, but personally I'd lean toward just keeping the strict name requirement (and simpler implementation) and just catch and report ""interface not found"" errors better.",{},,User,False
