13036,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-09 19:42:38+00:00,3845895,fastavro/fastavro,6951699,scottbelden,40203918,fastavro,207601759,403596956,"A `parse_schema` function was added in https://github.com/fastavro/fastavro/pull/237 and will return a parsed schema that can be passed in like you would a normal schema. This parsed schema will not be re-parsed and therefore reduces that cost.

For example:
```python
    from fastavro import writer, parse_schema

    schema = {...}
    records = [...]

    parsed_schema = parse_schema(schema)

    with open('weather.avro', 'wb') as out:
        writer(out, parsed_schema, records)
```",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
