13086,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-10 05:28:34+00:00,91379993,tensorflow/tensorboard,4221553,chihuahua,15658638,tensorflow,264079854,335364872,"Hi. Does these docs help? https://www.tensorflow.org/programmers_guide/embedding

Basically, you want to obtain your variable ... which *probably* looks like this.

```py
# Obtain the weights.
logits_weights = graph.get_tensor_by_name(
    'InceptionV3/Logits/Conv2d_1c_1x1/weights/ExponentialMovingAverage:0')
# Flatten the filters of the CNN if the tensor is 4D.
classes = logits_weights.shape_as_list()[-1]
logits_weights_flattened = tf.reshape(logits_weights, [-1, classes])
# [emb_size, classes] -> [classes, emb_size]
embeddings = tf.transpose(logits_weights_flattened)
embeddings_var = tf.get_variable(
    'embeddings',
    embeddings.shape_as_list(),
    trainable=False,
    # Prevent errors while computing PCA in the projector towards the start
    # of training.
    initializer=tf.random_normal_initializer())
```

Then, you want to configure a file with metadata ... something like this:

```py
metadata_file = os.path.join(self.output_dir, 'some_metadata.txt')
config = projector.ProjectorConfig()
emb_proj = config.embeddings.add()
emb_proj.tensor_name = embeddings_var.op.name
emb_proj.metadata_path = metadata_file
summary_writer = tf.summary.FileWriter(self.output_dir)
projector.visualize_embeddings(summary_writer, config)
```",{},MEMBER,User,False
