13923,IssueCommentEvent,2016-04-19 16:37:20+00:00,4744355,soft-matter/trackpy,8937919,caspervdw,5857177,soft-matter,99618251,212009016,"This sounds like a good idea to me! I like the analogy.

To suppress unexpected results (@nkeim ) we should be very specific and picky about the parameters given to any of the 'custom' functions. `locate` can on the other hand be more accomodating: we could even convert images to gray by default if necessary, etc.

