13928,IssueCommentEvent,2017-01-22 03:00:49+00:00,3602702,litl/rauth,7992169,TwoBitAlchemist,190361,litl,202355261,274304370,"The problem is [here](https://github.com/litl/rauth/blob/master/rauth/utils.py#L30). You are changing a dictionary as you are iterating over it. The dict type has been [reimplemented in Python 3.6](https://docs.python.org/3.6/whatsnew/3.6.html#whatsnew36-compactdict) to be more memory efficient, following an enhancement by the PyPy team. So something about this internal change has caused the `oauth_token_secret` key to get skipped by `parse_utf8_qsl` (it is not converted and is still bytes at the end). The solution should be to produce a new dict instead of trying to modify the one in place.",{},,User,False
