14109,IssueCommentEvent,2016-12-02 17:47:29+00:00,1126087,gitpython-developers/GitPython,501585,ankostis,503709,gitpython-developers,193026740,264516101,"We would have fixed it yesterday, if we could :-)

Just [search for `tag.leaks`](/gitpython-developers/GitPython/issues?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=label%3Atag.leaks%20) to get an idea of the invested effort  to reach to the point where git-python runs decently in *Windows*.

The 1st and easiest  fix is to [retrofit `git.Repo` as a context-manager](/ankostis/GitPython/commit/47f64422de0a252133b0222e64f35be9b8ad50ba), so instead of `try..finally` you would use it as `with Repo() as repo: ...`.",{},,User,False
