14300,IssueCommentEvent,2015-12-14 22:07:48+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,1695496,jbednar,6392739,conda,110714023,164575198,"@jdreaver, yes, some of these optional packages do require recompilation -- e.g. my example of Python with and without the readline support, which I believe requires linking it against a readline replacement library (non-GPL), and thus having an entirely separate binary.  There might be a combinatorial explosion of binaries required if there are multiple such C-library options, with every possible combination of included library needing a new compiled version.   So we probably could realistically only support optional C libraries in a very few cases, such as the very important readline case.  But I would think that most such optional libraries are simply things that pure Python code wraps in ""try: except:"", i.e. uses if it's there, ignores it otherwise.  I would hope that keeping track of those would be straightforward.",{},,User,False
