14350,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-24 21:57:14+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,10598343,mbargull,6392739,conda,231037587,303863305,"(Sorry, off topic, re logging:
>There are a lot of warnings in the debug output all the sudden. I don't know if it has to do with recent changes in logging setup

Probably those warnings were previously suppressed since `initialize_root_logger` had been implicitly called and set root's level to `ERROR` (from the default `WARNING`). The warnings stem from outside `'conda'`-logger domain, i.e., `'tests'`, and thus get handled by the root logger.
So now everything (with some exceptions until #5405 is ported to `4.4.x`) works as intended and those warnings are visible and can be fixed 😄 (or, as a last resort, if they're somehow not fixable, they may explicitly suppressed via filters or setting non-root logger level).)",{},,User,False
