14624,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-04 22:59:24+00:00,1404690,PmagPy/PmagPy,1278789,njarboe,16460206,PmagPy,226046051,299332197,"Thanks for the info @Caoimhinmg. I guess it makes more sense when you are getting new data you just call it Fit 1, Fit 2, etc because until you have done quite a few, you may not know what caused the components yet. Especially for you guys doing 0.5-1 Ga rocks. When I am loading studies already published, I know all the fits and just want to set them straight away. Maybe a feature for the future. ",{},,User,False
