14631,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-16 06:04:47+00:00,1404690,PmagPy/PmagPy,1836578,moonshoes87,16460206,PmagPy,226061227,301684352,"@njarboe, I just pushed a fix for this (basically reverting to @Caoimhinmg's original way of doing it, plus adding a warning that some measurements are being deleted).  With the data from OrgMagICFiles.zip, this means that 1747 measurements are excluded for lack of a location name.  There is only one site in the sites table, so there is only one available site --> location relationship.

However, I'm guessing that what you *really* want is not just a warning that says ""you are missing this many locations at the measurement level, so we are excluding these measurements"".  You really want a warning that says, (in this particular case), ""of the 41 sites you reference in the sample table, only 1 is present in the sites table"".  That way the user actually knows where data are missing and can fill them in accordingly.

Am I correct that this is the behavior you would ideally like?  It is a little bit tricky to implement this robustly, but I am guessing it would be useful.  






",{},,User,False
14634,IssueCommentEvent,2018-02-19 19:44:58+00:00,1404690,PmagPy/PmagPy,1836578,moonshoes87,16460206,PmagPy,296885151,366787104,"So maybe it is a MagIC upgrade issue after all?  Or is there something else to do on the PmagPy side?

