14867,IssueCommentEvent,2016-08-10 00:57:40+00:00,3510804,GalSim-developers/GalSim,1454906,rmandelb,1462196,GalSim-developers,168979100,238737347,"I would like some feedback from @rmjarvis and @jmeyers314 on this.  But for now, here are my thoughts:

- yes, analytic form for kValue and fillKValue.  This is useful as it means we get something exact when we're using DFT rendering.

- the way I normally think of kValue and fillKValue vs. xValue and fillXValue is that the former is required for DFT rendering of basic profiles, while the latter is needed for photon-shooting of basic profiles.  (By ""basic profiles"" I mean one term of a convolution, like a profile for a galaxy or for a PSF.  i.e., convolutions of a galaxy with a PSF don't tend to be analytic in real-space, but that's not a problem for photon-shooting, because you determine the photon offsets for each element of the convolution and then just add them.)  The reason we have a lot of infrastructure built around tabulating the Hankel transforms needed to write a Sersic profile in k-space is that most of our image rendering is done via DFT, which means that we needed a fast yet accurate way to do this.  That infrastructure includes the inclusion in the galsim.GSParams of tunable parameters that set the speed vs. accuracy tradeoff.  It also includes the possibility of caching the table so later Sersic profiles that get initialized with the same n can access the table and don't have to rebuild it.  This option is similar to your option (2) if you swap x<->k, but more powerful given the tunability of the speed vs. accuracy tradeoff.

- If I haven't over-simplified the situation regarding the need for ```kValue``` and ```xValue``` (hopefully @rmjarvis or @jmeyers314 will comment), then it seems to me that for the default drawing method, we can simply have ```xValue``` be undefined and set ```isAnalyticX``` to False.  If the profile is initialized and then the user tells it to render the image via photon-shooting, it can at that point build the lookup table needed for ```xValue``` and ```fillXValue``` (and cache it).",{},,User,False
14868,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-27 18:12:39+00:00,3510804,GalSim-developers/GalSim,1454906,rmandelb,1462196,GalSim-developers,274629033,347273319,"Thanks Bob!  I just approved the changes and it looks like Mike just did too, so we are good to go.  Maybe let's give it until tonight to let anybody else who wants to comment, and plan to merge first thing in the morning?

