15159,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-04 02:36:01+00:00,55808787,openthread/openthread,20312411,chshu,16142269,openthread,225999425,299084916,"@jwhui, Thanks a lot for the detailed clarification.

Given that there are many challenges to implement noise floor detection, I also prefer to use hardware-specific sensitivity value as the basic noise floor for link metric computation.

So I propose the following changes:
- Add `#define OPENTHREAD_CONFIG_RADIO_RECEIVE_SENSITIVITY -100` configuration
(platforms could define their own values separately, here I assume the sensitivity should be same among hardwares under the same platform, and does not change during runtime);
- Change `kDefaultNoiseFloor` to `kNoiseFloor` and set it to the receive sensitivity value;
- Simplify noise floor related implementation since we don't need it anymore.

@jwhui, @abtink, Please let me know if you have any suggestions, thanks.",{},,User,False
