15222,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-26 22:14:37+00:00,55808787,openthread/openthread,4838268,jhwoodyatt,16142269,openthread,236625268,311197292,"p1. I made a lot of editorial changes, but the technical changes to the existing hierarchy of files was limited to removing the number reservations for things that seemed specific to Thread by my reading of the text. I'm in the middle of composing the files that will contain the definitions of those numbers in the unified draft that are missing from the basis.

p2. I copied the files rather than edit them in place out of a concern for keeping the unified draft from being changed by my introduction of the basis draft. I was planning to track any new changes to the unified draft as other contributors make them until the day arrives when we feel comfortable that the basis and the Thread specialization are a suitable replacement for it.

p3. I can see how that might lead to confusion with other contributors, so an alternative to consider is that perhaps I should push this change now into the separate spinel-documentation repository, and track the changes to the unified draft in the current openthread repository until it can be deleted from the openthread source tree. Let's talk about that.",{},,User,False
