2. Rewriting the test for the setting of a custom path to extract FF from the path and see that it is then set from the right path is a test that would always fail on anything but linux, as the whole point of this patch is that selenium has quite some autodetection on where to find FF on Linux and Windows - but not on mac. See also: https://github.com/SeleniumHQ/selenium/issues/1128 . So what to do? I'd like to provide a test that I can a) test myself (mac user) and b) works on any platform so other people don't see spurious failures running the test. Also I'd like not to restrict the test to only darwin, so you can run it on the integration server.

3. I haven't yet pulled in mock, as @andrewsmedina hasn't yet said anything - in the meantime
   ```python
from contextlib import contextmanager
@contextmanager
def spy_on(an_object, slot_name, spy):
    original_value = getattr(an_object, slot_name)
    setattr(an_object, slot_name, spy)
    try:
        yield spy
    finally:
        setattr(an_object, slot_name, original_value)
```
isn't too bad I think, and should be quite easy to replace once you decide to pull in mock.

What do you think?",{},,User,False
