15531,IssueCommentEvent,2017-08-10 12:13:06+00:00,60273704,mozilla/DeepSpeech,5991088,tilmankamp,131524,mozilla,249026636,321533925,"@istojan Thanks for your description. I think I know what is going wrong here: Our batch system is based on continuing at the first sample, if there were not enough samples for a full batch. This produces duplicates in reports. There are two ways to avoid this: Either by making the reports unique in regards to the sample, or by changing the batch building process. The latter is already solved as part of my current code-refactoring that will introduce dynamic batch sizes.

For the moment [this code](https://github.com/mozilla/DeepSpeech/blob/master/DeepSpeech.py#L711-L719) could be changed to skip duplicates of `label` (using an additional set object for the labels).

Would you want to contribute this?
 
",{},,User,False
