15941,IssueCommentEvent,2016-10-02 14:43:53+00:00,3791384,coursera-dl/coursera-dl,22575512,k88albr,5588942,coursera-dl,160810670,250974770,"Thanks @balta2ar as of 10/1, still needed to change the script.  Several hoops to jump through to get this all working on OS X El Capitan, so putting in current steps for anyone else.
First installed python 3.52 from https://www.python.org/downloads/

Mostly followed @gokul-uf post here: https://github.com/coursera-dl/coursera-dl/issues/475

```
mkdir mycoursera; cd mycoursera
sudo pip install virtualenv
virtualenv -p /usr/local/bin/python3 coursera
cd coursera/
./bin/pip install coursera
cd ../
./coursera/bin/coursera-dl -u <email> -p <pass> course
```

Which failed with the cookies error.  

Wasn't sure where to find the file to change and found it here:

_./mycoursera/coursera/lib/python3.5/site-packages/coursera/coursera_dl.py_

And in this case, the call at line 1056 'download_class'

`            if download_class(args, class_name):
`

I changed to

  `          if download_on_demand_class(args, class_name):
`

Then it all worked, and I was able to dl the class, thank you so much!",{},,User,False
