15994,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-16 14:10:13+00:00,7137821,cloudtools/troposphere,638982,markpeek,3028687,cloudtools,234580784,309036069,"Sure, let me try to answer the questions.

1. The Cluster SecurityConfiguration [docs](http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/aws-resource-emr-cluster.html#cfn-emr-cluster-securityconfiguration) listed the type as ""String"". Also, AWS::EMR::SecurityConfiguration is a resource so it needs to be instantiated separately (as opposed to a property).
2. Looking at the [docs](http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/aws-resource-emr-securityconfiguration.html#w2ab2c19c12d512c13) for AWS::EMR::SecurityConfiguration we see there is a return value for Ref(). I ran a quick test and saw the Ref() on a SecurityConfiguration returns its name (either a constructed name or your own name through the Name property). I didn't need to do the Ref() as I could have hardcoded a name (String) but I thought it better to use Ref() in the example. (Note: the docs are wrong saying Ref() returns the cluster ID when it really returns the SecurityConfiguration name and I followed up with AWS about it.)",{},,User,False
