16204,IssueCommentEvent,2017-02-03 16:04:25+00:00,2527828,getsentry/raven-python,10265572,nnewman,1396951,getsentry,204172794,277287172,"@mitsuhiko - apparently I was too quick to close this. You are definitely correct regarding the error handler, however the hook into the Flask application logger still appears to be broken. I have updated my sample application and pasted below. Once again, on Flask v0.11.1, upon hitting `/log` I get an error in Sentry, however when I updated Flask to v0.12, I no longer saw an error appear in Sentry upon hitting that route.

```python
import logging

from flask import Flask, jsonify
from raven.contrib.flask import Sentry

sentry = Sentry()

def create_app():
    app = Flask(__name__)

    app.config['DEBUG'] = True

    sentry.init_app(
        app,
        dsn='https://<redacted>',
        logging=True,
        level=logging.DEBUG
    )

    @app.errorhandler(500)
    def internal_server_error(exception):
        return 'Internal Server Error'

    return app


app = create_app()


@app.route('/log')
def test_log():
    app.logger.error('TEST ERROR')
    return jsonify({'message': 'ok'})


@app.route('/')
def test_route():
    raise Exception('TEST')


if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run()
```",{},,User,False
