16207,IssueCommentEvent,2016-11-03 17:03:42+00:00,2527828,getsentry/raven-python,6073918,NovaDev94,1396951,getsentry,182060170,258206739,"I have the same problem with this. I'm not sure if this is the same case as yours. 

With Celery workers with `maxtasksperchild=X`, when it reaches the Xth-task (the worker will be reloaded after finishing this task), it's like the Worker exits too early so that the default `threaded` logger hasn't finished sending the errors yet.  

Changing the transport to `sync` works wonderfully (though it isn't as efficient).  ",{},,User,False
