16371,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-06 00:03:14+00:00,71932349,ray-project/ray,2560516,stephanie-wang,22125274,ray-project,311807024,379111537,"Looks like the message type is `protocol::MessageType_DisconnectClient`, defined in `node_manager.fbs`. The `ClientConnection` class sets this message type if there's an error reading from the socket ([code](https://github.com/ray-project/ray/blob/master/src/ray/common/client_connection.cc#L105)). We should replace [this handler](https://github.com/ray-project/ray/blob/master/src/ray/object_manager/object_manager.cc#L428) with the common `protocol::MessageType_DisconnectClient`, instead of the custom one defined for the object manager. @elibol, can you take care of this?

