16438,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-24 16:15:43+00:00,71932349,ray-project/ray,21118851,simon-mo,22125274,ray-project,325930322,391773570,"- Redis is doable. 
- Should we really override? This will incur cache lookup overhead each remote call. To avoid this overhead, we will override ray.remote so that one can do `@ray.remote(memoize=True)`. However, compare:
```
@memoize
@ray.remote
def func
```
I still think an explicit memoize decorator works best for our use case because for now, we just need to memoize the functions that we anticipate temporal redundancy. 
- A better implementation (probably requires touching ray core) would requires asynchronous cache lookup and killing or canceling task as needed. ",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
