16728,IssueCommentEvent,2018-06-26 21:36:03+00:00,26877260,Microsoft/ApplicationInsights-Python,530988,letmaik,6154722,Microsoft,335835522,400470741,"One gotcha was related to the strange auto generated contract classes:
```py
    @properties.setter
    def properties(self, value):
        """"""The properties property.
        
        Args:
            value (hash). the property value.
        """"""
        if value == self._defaults['properties'] and 'properties' in self._values:
            del self._values['properties']
        else:
            self._values['properties'] = value
```
This led to problems when assigning `{}` which is equal to the default and then resulted in a new instance the next time `data.properties` was accessed.",{},MEMBER,User,False
