16863,IssueCommentEvent,2016-01-11 16:20:04+00:00,34906350,BlueBrain/NeuroM,15011025,eleftherioszisis,1479142,BlueBrain,125964722,170602463,"Well, I am not sure how biologists and especially the experimentalists fit in that requires a mathematical background :P 

As far as I know from people of the lab that tried to use NeuroM, iterators were not intuitive and by extension hard to use. This is the main reason that some prefer to stick with Pneumatk, even though it is not tested...

Unfortunately, whether we like it or not, we have to take into account the difficulty of the software for the groups that we are targeting, because NeuroM is not destined only for interior use. And to be honest I think that the user should not go around searching for the correct function of the correct object to apply the calculation of choice.. :/ (I like the semantic association though for it links the functions with their respective objects!)",{},,User,False
