17125,IssueCommentEvent,2016-08-03 22:35:45+00:00,27921304,Polyconseil/zbarlight,694541,rbarrois,818669,Polyconseil,169142715,237396497,"Hi,

You seem to have a file named ``zbarlight.py`` in your local folder.
Thus, when running ``import zbarlight``, Python imports the *local* file instead of the ``zbarlight`` module.

However, that code is, in turn, importing ``zbarlight`` — itself.

Try renaming that file to, for instance, ``zbarlight_demo.py``; that should fix your issue.",{},,User,False
