17191,IssueCommentEvent,2018-06-06 17:32:04+00:00,5888353,spotify/luigi,1725061,cabouffard,251374,spotify,209951482,395150875,"@dlstadther Hey! I'm unsure if you're the right person to ask but I was wondering if something could be done with this PR as this is a great  behavior to have!

I've been able to see this issue requesting this behavior: https://github.com/spotify/luigi/issues/2354 and there are 2 persons that have thumbs-up the PR.

In the story linked above, @Tarrasch  mention that this behavior is something offered by ConfigParser by default, but it isn't. 

Looking around from different posts and thread resolution on the internet, the fix is to pass the `os.environ` value to the ConfigParser so that it has access to the environment variable.

Let me know if you need additional informations fron us, as suspect this additions to cause no harm and that even though the function says it's deprecated, this the the main entry point to load the configuration object throughout the Luigi codebase.

Please let us know if there is another way to load environment variables into the configuration file that we may not be aware of.

