17415,IssueCommentEvent,2017-08-02 18:02:30+00:00,68402336,streamlink/streamlink,1396878,gravyboat,22243823,streamlink,238308624,319751025,"@techmouse To me at least it's that we need to do OUR best to do what is right when we can for people using the service legitimately. Simply because someone else is doing something shady (which is one of the reasons I only use Streamlink to stream direct sources such as Twitch, Youtube, Mixer, Crunchyroll, etc.) by re-streaming content doesn't mean we have to spite them on top of it. Let's be honest, 75% of the plugins would have to be cut if we disallowed sites that had the potential to be re-streaming instead of streaming original content/commentary.

There may only be one legitimate streamer on Vaughnlive, I don't know, I don't use the site, but is it fair of us to negatively impact that one person who might rely on their income from this source? I don't think so. I would rather we take action to protect a single individual using a streaming platform as their source of income/anti-depressant/whatever than allow that platform to be shut down because of shady re-streams. Those are on the site maintainer to address. It's a tough spot to be in for sure.",{},,User,False
