17454,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-09 00:16:36+00:00,68402336,streamlink/streamlink,16033421,beardypig,22243823,streamlink,324993142,403328701,"@kuon good idea :) It might work - entire segments would have to be skipped. In twitch’s case that would be a second or two. The problem is that it might corrupt the stream and cause issues for some players, but if it is an option with sufficient warnings that should be up to the user. (Of course, there will always be people that don’t read those warnings...)
It is unlikely that streamlink will have extra video buffered though, is more likely the case that twitch has got ahead because one segment of video took a bit longer than expected to download and he video paused for a second. But, future I downloaded segments could be skipped to catch up - to maintain the live edge. ",{},MEMBER,User,False
