17667,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-14 22:42:34+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,649860,SwartzCr,17889013,certbot,273162880,344424468,"Hmm, this is interesting.
The complexity with this is that we want to be able to handle many different pre- and post- hooks. We do some batching of them to ensure that hooks like `service apache restart` aren't called too many times.
Where you might be generating different authz - I think we may only confirm your Let's Encrypt account once. This would make it hard to determine which pre-hook to run in the case where you had multiple.
I think ultimately @bmw is the one who could comment on whether we'd take a PR for this kind of thing. I think we're probably unlikely to make a new flag for hooks of this sort, but there may be an easy way for you to wrap certbot in something that handles your firewall. Then again maybe this isn't the first time that we've gotten someone asking about this, so I'll leave it to @bmw to comment - though he's out for the week, so the soonest answer would be on Monday.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
