17673,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-13 19:12:52+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,6504915,bmw,17889013,certbot,265255223,336542756,"What's the output of `sudo service apache2 start`? If it's still unable to obtain port 443, do you know if your Apache configuration was previously listening on this port? Do you know what's listening on this port now (possibly by using instructions provided [here](https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/106561/finding-the-pid-of-the-process-using-a-specific-port))?

If Apache wasn't previously listening on port 443 on your server or you're not sure if it was, please provide the full log corresponding to the output above. Logs are stored in `/var/log/letsencrypt` by default. Feel free to redact domains, e-mail and IP addresses as you see fit.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
