17780,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-18 09:17:31+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,1006726,sthen,17889013,certbot,324247766,390147922,"Hi (OpenBSD port maintainer here). I just tested with a clean OpenBSD 6.3 installation. Steps were: install OpenBSD, login as root, pkg_add certbot, run ""certbot certonly"". This starts up okay so I don't think there is a general issue with the package or dependencies.

I'll go for the most likely causes first:

- Was the machine upgraded from a previous OpenBSD version? If so, did you remember to update all packages (pkg_add -u)?

- Is there anything strange in your shell environment when running this? Try ""env -i certbot"".

If these don't help, please post a bit more information about how the machine is setup and output from the following commands (in full, don't trim):

```
$ pkg_info
$ env LD_DEBUG=1 python2.7 -c 'from cryptography.hazmat.bindings._openssl import ffi, lib'
$ dmesg
```

I don't think this is a certbot problem as such, so it's probably best to take this to ports@openbsd.org where more people who can help are likely to see it.",{},NONE,User,False
