17896,IssueCommentEvent,2016-06-14 17:17:52+00:00,39848792,rtfd/recommonmark,1306044,pfultz2,366329,rtfd,100648424,225951852,"Ok, so I updated the parser to use `pending_xref` for references in this branch [here](https://github.com/pfultz2/recommonmark/tree/pending-xref). However, it requires sphinx to be updated with this pull request [here](https://github.com/sphinx-doc/sphinx/pull/2644).

For links that use `http://` or `https://`, it still uses `docutils.nodes.reference`, since they are external but other links are added using `pending_xref` with the type set to `any`. This is really nice, and allows me to cross reference more than just documents.

Once the pull request is merged into sphinx, I can send a pull request for this as well(although sphinx has yet to respond to my pull request).",{},,User,False
