18116,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-21 19:49:16+00:00,49976939,learningequality/kolibri,163966,ivanistheone,3926525,learningequality,299795423,375073223,"I ran into the disappearing channel bug again today (Updating a channel with a single exercise node in removes it from Kolibri installed channels).

It seems the ""already on your device"" logic used during content update is not working 100%, at least not for exercise nodes.

I was able to ""break"" a channel during UPDATE. I had modified an exercise (which changes the perseus json file for the question), but the import wizard showed the channel as ""No changes""

After this partial-Update, going to the exercise under `/learn` shows an error in the browser, presumably because it's trying to load a perseus.json file it hasn't synced.

<img width=""859"" alt=""screen shot 2018-03-21 at 3 48 20 pm"" src=""https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/163966/37733713-5ed2a6c4-2d1f-11e8-956f-04fc1bc68323.png"">


I guess what's going on is:
  - the node is marked as available since the exercise + associated perseus files was previous imported
  - the first part of the channel update process updates the DB tables
  - by not doing the second part of the channel update (importing the files), we end up with a broken state since `assessment_item_ids` column in `content_assessmentmetadata` points to file that doesn't exist.





",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
