18335,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-02 18:39:52+00:00,34864402,apache/incubator-mxnet,568948,piiswrong,47359,apache,310180524,378005952,"We should raise a warning when assign blocks with non-matching prefix.
In python copy on assignment only happens for builtin types. This kind of hidden protocol that decides when to copy is a hack.

Also `net2.block1 = net1.block1` itself is a hack. The right approach is to define a new block and compose them.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
